  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a large baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong>, your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the wedges are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666709627386-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666709627386-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666709627386-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666709627386-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1666709627386-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> potatoes </strong>(skins on)<strong> </strong>into bite-sized pieces and add<strong> </strong>to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover with <strong>cling film</strong>, pierce a few holes in the top with a fork and put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 8-9 min or until fork tender</p><p>Once cooked, carefully remove the cling film and leave the potatoes to cool for 2-3 min then mash together</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666709631618-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666709631618-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666709631618-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666709631618-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1666709631618-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweet potatoes are cooking, zest your<strong> lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Chop half the <strong>lime[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>wedges</p><p>Trim, then finely slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
